      "creatureType": "",
      "blurb": "Male gnome psychotic barbarian",
      "publicNotes": "<h3>Conversion notes (this module)</h3><p><strong>Role:</strong> Pilts's executioner — a tongueless, one-eyed gnome berserker who calls the Emperor 'Unca Pit' and loves the guillotine like a pet. <strong>He never attacks gnomes</strong> unless struck first (Pilts knows never to order it). Understanding his babbling takes @Check[type:society|dc:20] (or Sense Motive at the GM's whim).</p><p><strong>Morale:</strong> fights to the death. If Pilts dies he freezes a round in shock, then resumes. If Pilts <strong>surrenders</strong> in his presence, Jabbyr snaps and attacks the ex-emperor for treason — and may demand the PCs help him strap 'Unca Pit' into the Tall Knife.</p>",
      "privateNotes": ""
    },
